## Mock Mode for Development

### ✅ Implement useful mocks:
```python
def _generate_mock_test_cases(self, requirements: str) -> list[TestCaseDraft]:
    """
    Generate contextual mock test cases for development.
    
    Analyzes keywords in requirements to produce relevant mocks.
    """
    req_lower = requirements.lower()
    test_cases = []
    
    # Keyword-based mock generation
    if any(kw in req_lower for kw in ["login", "auth", "password"]):
        test_cases.extend(self._auth_test_cases())
    
    if any(kw in req_lower for kw in ["search", "filter", "query"]):
        test_cases.extend(self._search_test_cases())
    
    if any(kw in req_lower for kw in ["form", "submit", "input"]):
        test_cases.extend(self._form_test_cases())
    
    # Default cases if no keywords matched
    if not test_cases:
        test_cases = self._generic_test_cases()
    
    return test_cases
```

